### Project Overview

The project implements a web application designed to run as a **Databricks App**. Databricks Apps are Python web applications configured via an `app.yaml` file (Databricks Asset Bundle format). This app provides Unity Catalog and general Databricks-related services, focusing on metadata management, governance, and operational tools.

### Core Features

- **Data Contracts:** Instrument Data Products with technical metadata based on the Open Data Contract Standard. Managed by `DataContractsManager`. Includes schema validation, quality checks, access control verification, sample data display, etc.
    - Data Contracts can be written in any text format (plain text, YAML, JSON). For structured formats, the BITOL ODCS standard is supported (https://github.com/bitol-io/open-data-contract-standard/blob/main/schema/odcs-json-schema-latest.json).
- **Data Products:** Group Databricks assets (tables, views, functions, models, dashboards, jobs, notebooks) using tags (e.g., `data-product-name`, `data-product-domain`). Managed by `DataProductsManager`. Follows the BITOL ODPS specification (https://github.com/bitol-io/open-data-product-standard/blob/main/schema/odps-json-schema-latest.json).
- **Datasets:** *(DEPRECATED — replaced by the ontology-driven Asset model)* Physical implementations of Data Contracts. Previously managed by `DatasetsManager`, now stored as Asset entities with `asset_type="Dataset"`. Legacy routes at `/api/datasets` remain for backward compatibility but will be removed. Use `/api/assets` instead.
- **Assets & Ontology:** Generic, ontology-driven entity model replacing bespoke tables for datasets, tables, views, etc. Asset types are defined in `src/backend/src/data/taxonomies/ontos-ontology.ttl` and synced at startup. Managed by `AssetsManager` and `OntologySchemaManager`. Cross-entity relationships use `EntityRelationshipDb`. The Asset Explorer UI provides a unified view across all asset types with persona-based visibility filtering.
- **Tagging System:** Unified tagging via `EntityTagAssociationDb` for ALL entity types. See `03-system-components-and-requirements.mdc` for details.
- **Business Glossaries:** Hierarchical glossaries per organizational unit (company, LOB, department, team, project). Merged bottom-up for users, allowing overrides. Terms have tags, markdown descriptions, lifecycle status, assigned assets. Managed by `BusinessGlossariesManager`.
- **Master Data Management (MDM):** Integrates with Zingg.ai for MDM capabilities. Managed by `MasterDataManagementManager`.
- **Entitlements:** Combines access privileges into personas (roles) and assigns them to directory groups. Managed by `EntitlementsManager`.
- **Security:** Enables advanced security features (e.g., differential privacy) on assets. Managed by `SecurityFeaturesManager`.
- **Compliance:** Define and verify compliance rules, calculating an overall score. Managed by `ComplianceManager`.
- **Catalog Commander:** Norton Commander-inspired dual-pane explorer for managing catalog assets (copy/move tables/schemas). Managed by `CatalogCommanderManager`.
- **Data Asset Reviews:** Workflow for reviewing and approving assets (tables, views, functions). Managed by `DataAssetReviewManager`. Includes notifications for reviewers/requesters.
- **Settings:** Configure app settings, Databricks connection, Git integration, background jobs, and RBAC (Roles). Managed by `SettingsManager`.

### General Usage

- Users see different features in the UI based on their group memberships. Admin = read/write everything. Data Producer = read/write Data Contracts and Products. Data Consumer = read-only Data Products and Contracts.
- The **Home Page** is persona-aware: Consumers get a marketplace-style discovery surface; Producers get options to create/continue draft products and contracts.
- Data Product creation flow (high level): Producer + Consumer co-design a draft Data Contract → Producer enriches and releases the contract → Producer builds and releases a Data Product whose output ports reference the contract → Consumer subscribes, creating a tracked linkage → background compliance jobs verify the contract over time and notify stakeholders on violations.
- Data Governance role users maintain Data Domains and Business Glossaries that classify Products and Contracts.

For the full data product lifecycle theory and roles & responsibilities, see `docs/user-journeys/`.
